\f0\fs28 \cf0 Styles allow you to save and apply formatting to text. For example, you could create a \'93Block Quote\'94 style with an indent and a smaller font than the rest of the text (Scrivener in fact provides a \'93Block Quote\'94 style by default).\
Scrivener remembers the style associated with a section of text. This way, if you change the formatting of a style, Scrivener can update all text that uses that style to use the new formatting.\
