\f2\b\fs36 Applying Styles\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_H::1><!$Scr_Ps::0>
\f0\fs28 To apply a style, do one of the following:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Select a style from the styles menu in the format bar\'97the styles menu is indicated by a pilcrow (\'b6)  and an \'93a\'94.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Ctrl-click on the text and choose the style from the contextual menu that appears.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Go to 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f3\b Format > Style
\f1\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28  in the main menu and choose a style.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Go to 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f3\b Format > Style > Show Styles Pane
\f1\b0 \cf2 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f3\b l
\f0\b0\fs28 \cf0  and choose a style from the panel that appears.\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 There are two types of style:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}
\f2\b Paragraph Styles
\f0\b0  get applied to whole paragraphs, and include paragraph formatting such as line spacing and indents. They can optionally include character formatting such as italics and bold, and can also optionally affect the font family and size.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\li1440\fi-1440\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	
\f4 \uc0\u8259 
\f0 	}Paragraph styles are indicated in menus by a pilcrow icon.\
{\listtext	
\f4 \uc0\u8259 
\f0 	}Paragraph styles that also include character formatting are indicated by a pilcrow icon and an \'93a\'94.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	2.	}
\f2\b Character Styles
\f0\b0  get applied only to the selected text or current word (if there is no selection). They only include character formatting such as italics and bold (and optionally the font family and size). They do not include paragraph formatting such as line spacing and indents.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\li1440\fi-1440\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	
\f4 \uc0\u8259 
\f0 	}Character styles are indicated in menus by an \'93a\'94.\

