\f5\i\b Tip:
\f1\i0\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f0\fs28  For body text, it\'92s generally best to use \'93No Style\'94. In Scrivener, unlike in many word processors, you should apply styles only to text that you want formatted differently from everything else. If you use styles for everything, even the main body text, then you will make it harder for Compile to override your formatting for different output requirements.\cell \lastrow\row
