\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_H::1><!$Scr_Ps::0>
\f0\fs28 Sometimes you will want to tweak a style\'97maybe you realise you want your block quotes indented further, for instance. To do so, follow all the same steps as for creating styles above, except that instead of choosing 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f3\b New Style From Selection
\f1\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28  from the 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f3\b Style
\f1\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28  menu, choose 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f3\b Redefine Style From Selection
\f1\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28 .\
